title: cordova: copyLibs adds all dependencies from projects
message:
cordova: copyLibs adds all dependencies from projects

To update the dependencies in the cordova plugin, run :cordova:copyLibs
(and update the plugin.xml if the version has changed.
also remove old libs if the version has changed).

This is a workaround for simply having an 'aar' dependency.
The 'a' alias from tools/bash.inc automates the deployment
of updated libs, so I can iterate quickly on the cordova plugin ...

title: client: wire value
message:
client: wire value

Numbers are looking good ... with factored headers, compressed wire value
is about 1/3-1/4 the size of compressed json, with significally less
expansion bloat (wire value remains compact in memory and lazily parsed,
so not a blow up of objects in memory).
